OF THE HAEMATOPODEs, mon PLINv.

The Haematopus has its bill and very long legs red, and is much less than the Porphyrio, though of the same height of leg. It is native in Egypt. It stands on three toes to a foot; Hies are its favourite sood. It lives in Italy but 3 few dayS.

There is in marshy places in England 3 certain bird with long red legS, called Redshank in our tongue, but whether the description of the Haematopus of Pliny agrees with this or not let those who live in England seek out and enquire.
